    "chemicalDescription": [
      "s-Spider Pentapeptide-2 is a single chain peptide consisting of glycine, glutamine, and proline. It is synthetically produced based on a sequence from Spidroin 2 found in the spider, Nephila clavipes. The parent protein contains a maximum of 627 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence from the 20 standard amino acids."
